title: Rocky Landscape
description: A panoramic view of a rocky landscape, featuring numerous large stones scattered across the ground. The scene is set against a backdrop of distant mountains and a clear blue sky, suggesting a serene and natural environment.

title: River Landscape
description: A scenic view of a river winding through a landscape. The water appears to have a light greenish hue, contrasting with the reddish-brown rocky riverbed. On either side of the river, there are patches of greenery, including trees and shrubs, indicating a natural environment. The background features a mix of trees and possibly distant mountains, suggesting a serene and picturesque setting.

title: Aerial View of Coastal Area
description: This image shows an aerial view of a coastal region, featuring a mix of urban areas and natural landscapes. The land is divided into green areas, likely representing forests or parks, and urban development with visible roads and buildings. The coastline is marked by water bodies, with a prominent bay or inlet visible on the right side of the image.

title: Geometric Shape
description: A simple geometric design featuring a white line forming an L-shape on a black background.

title: Water Cycle and Landscape Illustration
description: An illustration depicting the water cycle in a mountainous landscape. On the left, dark clouds release rain over a mountain, with arrows indicating precipitation. Water flows down the mountain through rivers, shown in red, towards the beach on the right. The beach leads to the ocean, where the sun shines brightly above, and birds are seen flying in the sky. The ground is layered, showing soil and rock beneath the surface.

title: Abstract Line Design
description: A simple abstract design featuring a white line that forms a corner shape against a black background.

title: Geological Cross-Section
description: An illustrated geological cross-section showing a landscape with mountains, rivers, and valleys above ground, and a detailed view of the Earth's layers below. The top part features lush greenery, flowing water, and snow-capped mountains, while the bottom part reveals geological formations, including rock layers and fault lines.
